  "prompt": "Will doing organic chemistry from Ncert enough for Neet 17?",
  "response": "No, doing organic chemistry solely from NCERT is **not enough** to score well in NEET for organic chemistry and to confidently answer a substantial portion of organic chemistry questions in NEET 2027. Here's why:\n\n*   **NEET Level is Higher:** While NCERT is the foundation, NEET questions go beyond direct recall and require application of concepts. You'll need to understand reaction mechanisms, be able to predict products in complex reactions, and solve multi-concept based questions.\n\n*   **Incomplete Mechanisms:** NCERT often presents reactions without fully explaining the mechanisms. Understanding the mechanism is crucial for problem-solving and applying concepts to unfamiliar reactions.\n\n*   **Limited Problem-Solving:** NCERT has limited practice problems, especially of the type and difficulty level seen in NEET. You'll need extensive practice to develop problem-solving skills and speed.\n\n*   **Certain Concepts and Reactions are Not Covered:** NCERT might skip over certain named reactions or concepts that are included in the NEET syllabus.\n\n**What you NEED to do:**\n\n1.  **NCERT as the Base:**  Thoroughly understand NCERT. Memorize reactions, reagents, and their roles.  Solve all the in-text and exercise questions.\n\n2.  **Reference Book/Coaching Material:** Use a good reference book or study material from a reputable coaching institute. This will provide:\n    *   **Detailed explanations:**  Deeper explanations of mechanisms, more examples, and solved problems.\n    *   **Broader coverage:** Fill the gaps in NCERT and cover all topics in the NEET syllabus.\n    *   **Varied Problems:** A large number of practice questions of varying difficulty levels.\n    *   **Conceptual clarity:** Provides clearer, more comprehensive explanations.\n\n3.  **Practice, Practice, Practice:** Solve a LOT of questions. This is the most important thing. Solve past year NEET papers, sample papers, and chapter-wise question banks.  Focus on understanding *why* you are getting questions wrong.\n\n4.  **Focus on Reaction Mechanisms:** Understanding reaction mechanisms is KEY to solving NEET questions.\n\n5.  **Regular Revision:** Organic chemistry requires constant revision to retain reactions and concepts.\n\n**In summary:**\n\nNCERT is *essential* as a starting point, but it's definitely *not sufficient*. Use it as a base and supplement it with other resources and extensive problem-solving. A focused and comprehensive approach is needed to achieve a good score in NEET organic chemistry.\n",
